USING THE NEW GIT SITES

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

1. Creating a New Post

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

Every time you want to add a new project, audit, or lab report, you use the hugo new command.

On your Kali machine:
Bash

cd ~/cyber-portfolio  # Or whichever site you want to update
hugo new posts/target-machine-exploit.md
hugo new posts/network-recon-study.md

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
2. The "Visibility" Check (Crucial)
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

As we discussed, Hugo won't show the post unless you tell it the post is ready. Open each new file:
Bash

mousepad content/posts/target-machine-exploit.md

Change draft: true to draft: false. If you leave it as true, the post will exist in your folder but will be invisible on the website.


+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
How Hugo Displays Them
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

You don't need to create a new "Link" for every post.

    The Home Page: Most themes (like PaperMod) will automatically show a list of your most recent posts on the front page.

    The Archive: If you have many posts, Hugo creates a "Posts" section. If you visit your-site.com/posts/, you will see every single article you've ever written.

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

4. Organizing with Categories and Tags

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

To keep your portfolio professional, you should categorize your posts. You do this in the Frontmatter (the top of the .md file).

Example for a Cyber Lab post:
YAML

---
title: "Metasploit Exploitation Lab"
date: 2026-03-27
draft: false
tags: ["Metasploit", "Penetration Testing", "Kali Linux"]
categories: ["Lab Reports"]
---

Example for an SEO post:
YAML

---
title: "E-commerce Site Audit"
date: 2026-03-27
draft: false
tags: ["Keyword Research", "On-Page SEO"]
categories: ["Case Studies"]
---

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

5. Updating the Live Site

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

Whenever you finish writing your new posts on Kali, the process is always the same three steps:
Bash

git add .
git commit -m "Added two new lab reports"
git push

Since you set up the credential.helper store earlier, you won't have to type your password this time!
Pro-Tip: Adding Images to Posts

If you take a screenshot of a terminal exploit or an SEO dashboard:

    Place the image in static/images/my-screenshot.png.

    In your Markdown file, display it like this:
    ![Description of Image](/images/my-screenshot.png)
    
    
