Enable Search in hugo.toml

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

Open your configuration file on Kali:
Bash

mousepad ~/resume/hugo.toml  # Or whichever site you want to add search to

Add these lines to the bottom of the file:
Ini, TOML

[outputs]
    home = ["HTML", "RSS", "JSON"]

[[menu.main]]
    name = "Search"
    url = "search/"
    weight = 50

    Why this works: Hugo needs to create a search.json file (the "index") so it can look through your posts instantly. The [[menu.main]] part adds a clickable "Search" link to your top navigation bar.
    
    +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

2. Create the Search Page

++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

Now you need to create the actual page where the search bar will live. Run this in your terminal:
Bash

hugo new search.md

Now, edit that new file:
Bash

mousepad content/search.md

Replace everything in that file with this exact code:
YAML

---
title: "Search"
layout: "search"
summary: "search"
placeholder: "Search my projects, labs, or audits..."
---

(Note: You don't need draft: false here because the layout: "search" tells PaperMod to make it live immediately.)
3. Push the Changes

Since you saved your credentials earlier, this will be fast:
Bash

git add .
git commit -m "Add search functionality"
git push

4. How it looks on your phone

Since you asked about your phone earlier, this is a great feature to test there. Once the GitHub Action turns green:

    Open your site on your phone.

    You will see a new "Search" link in the menu.

    Tap it and type a keyword like "Metasploit" or "SEO."

    The results will pop up instantly without the page even reloading.
    
    
