Pro-Tip: Adding "Social Media" Icons

_++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++


Since this is a resume and portfolio, you likely want people to find your LinkedIn or GitHub easily. You can add these to your hugo.toml under [params]:
Ini, TOML

[[params.socialIcons]]
    name = "github"
    url = "https://github.com/XBlankZGap"
[[params.socialIcons]]
    name = "linkedin"
    url = "https://linkedin.com/in/your-profile"
    
    
    Hugo automatically looks into your content/posts/ folder. It takes every .md file that has draft: false and lists them one after another.
If you want a "Real" Homepage File

If you don't like that the theme is doing it automatically and you want a specific file you can edit for the homepage (like your experience.md file), you can create a special file:
Bash

# Run this on Kali in your project folder
mousepad content/_index.md

Anything you write in _index.md will become the "Body" of your homepage. * If you don't create this file: Hugo just shows your recent posts.

    If you do create this file: Hugo shows whatever text you put inside it plus your recent posts.
    
    
